{
  "name": "Illusionary Theorist",
  "type": "feat",
  "img": "icons/magic/symbols/runes-star-magenta.webp",
  "system": {
    "description": {
      "value": "<p>Category: Genjutsu </p><p>Prerequisite: Wisdom or Charisma 15+, Proficiency in Illusions </p><p>You study the Illusionary arts, gaining the following benefits: </p><p>• Increase your Wisdom or Charisma score by 1, to a maximum of 20.</p><p>• Reduce the Downtime required to Learn, Modify, and Create Genjutsu by 1 week, to a minimum of 1 week.</p><p>• Over the course of a short rest, you attempt to theorize and bend the chakra flow of Genjutsu you know to be more effective.</p><p> Select a number of Genjutsu you know equal to your Wisdom or Charisma modifier (Max. 4) and make an Wisdom or Charisma (Illusions) check for each jutsu.</p><p> The DC for each check is based on the rank of the jutsu (D-Rank: 16, C-Rank: 17, B-Rank: 18, A-Rank: 19, S-Rank: 20).</p><p> On a success, until your next rest, each selected jutsu is always under one of the following Onijutsu from the Kurama Clan at no additional chakra cost (you may choose a different Onijutsu for each jutsu).</p><p> - Careful Onijutsu (Max of 3 creatures.) </p><p> - Overwhelming Onijutsu </p><p> - Tenacious Onijutsu </p><p> - Subtle Onijutsu</p>",
      "chat": ""
    },
